libburn
________________________________________________________________________________

libburn is a library by which preformatted data get onto optical media: CD,
DVD, BD (Blu-Ray). On Linux it uses either /dev/sgN (on kernel 2.4 with
ide-scsi, or optional with concurrent operation of multiple drives) or
/dev/srM (kernel 2.6 and newer), /dev/hdX ( on kernel 2.6). On FreeBSD it uses
/dev/cdN, eventually via atapicam. On Solaris addresses look like
/dev/rdsk/cXtYd0s2. [0]

Upstream: https://dev.lovelyhq.com/libburnia/web/wiki/Libburn


